window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>I'm far from done.</b></p> <p>I gave Eris the first taste of the terror to come, but in doing so, I had to agree to a peace treaty with the King. For the next twelve years, I cannot bring as much as a single unit on human lands…</p> <p>That doesn't mean I'm going to rest, oh no! I will use that time to further build my skills and my kingdom. I need to become even stronger so I can bring Eris one step closer to total annihilation.</p> <p>There's a little problem, though… Where am I to find Discordance now that I can't terrorize Tague anymore? It seems like I will have to move to Lepidonia, land of vampires and lycanthropes, and take on whatever contracts I can find in exchange for Shards.</p> <p>As always, my eagerness will come back to bite me in the rear as I start hunting down wild entities that prove more than I bargained for.</p>"; 
